However, laws like the **Federal Trade Commission (FTC) Act** prohibit deceptive or unfair practices. If the software is defective, misrepresented, or fails to work as promised, you may have grounds to request a refund, depending on the circumstances. Some states, like California, have stricter consumer protection laws that may offer additional rights.

At Contoso, our refund policy for downloaded software states that refunds are generally not provided unless the software is found faulty or the purchase violates our terms. For more details or specific situations, please review our terms or contact customer support."}

